  "text": "The present study sought to expand on the findings of previous studies which have examined the productions of /s/ and /$/ by children with CIs. Studies have shown that children who use CIs produce less acoustic contrast than children with NH when attempting to produce /s/ and /$/ [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . In these studies, all productions of target /s/ and /$/ were included in the acoustic analyses as long as the attempts were fricatives.",
